# AgentScope

When the user asks for an AgentScope report or agent workspace inspection:

- Confirm the AgentScope CLI is installed with `agentscope --version`.
- If missing, tell the user before running `npm install -g github:WangHopeDream/agentscope`.
- Run `agentscope scan <workspace-root> --html --lang zh` for an interactive report.
- Use `--project-only` when the user wants project-local files only.
- Return the generated report path and summarize adapters, rules, skills, commands, configs, diagnostics, and child repositories.

Do not reimplement the scanner in the rule. The core CLI owns scanning and rendering.
